### LEXICON/PRONUNCIATION DICTIONARY
# To use for training ASR system WITH vowel length contrast
Directory: lang_o3g_LengthContrast
Files: lexicon.txt (lexicon)
Description: lexicon contains words and their respective pronunciation (/a/,/e/,/E/,/o/,/O/ labelled to distinct short/long vowels) using SAMPA symbols. Built from the concatenation of Fal et al. [1] and Diouf [2] dictionaries (about 8,724 entries), plus unknown words automatically phonetized using a G2P model [3].

[1] Fal, A., Santos, R., and Doneux, J. L. (1990). Dictionnaire wolof-français: suivid'un index françis-wolof. Karthala.
[2] Diouf, J. L. (2003). Dictionnaire wolof-français et français-wolof. KARTHALA Editions
[3] https://github.com/AdolfVonKleist/Phonetisaurus

